1
00:00:00,208 --> 00:00:01,500
Allie, my girlfriend.

2
00:00:01,501 --> 00:00:02,419
Do you know her?

3
00:00:02,420 --> 00:00:03,586
What happened, Sir Handsome?

4
00:00:03,628 --> 00:00:05,170
Are you okay? I’ll give you a ride.

5
00:00:05,171 --> 00:00:06,505
No, let’s go to the after party.

6
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:07,382
Just call me Tantan.

7
00:00:07,424 --> 00:00:09,842
From now on, we’re best friends.

8
00:00:09,843 --> 00:00:12,053
Did you enjoy the foam party last night?

9
00:00:12,095 --> 00:00:14,723
I didn’t come to Siargao to party, actually.

10
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:17,975
I need you to hire the best tour guide in General Luna.

11
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:18,768
[HAN BIN] You’re lucky.

12
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:20,728
Because we have the best tour guide

13
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:22,188
in the entire Siargao!

14
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:23,356
She’s here!

15
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:24,524
Kara, Jao.

16
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:25,191
[SIARGOANON] Karajaw!

17
00:00:25,192 --> 00:00:26,526
Please help me find Allie.

18
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:28,403
[KARA] I still don’t know how we’ll find

19
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:29,696
your ex-girlfriend.

20
00:00:29,946 --> 00:00:30,822
Fiancée.

21
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:31,865
Ex-fiancée.

22
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:34,242
Allie and I started dating in college.

23
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:35,493
I thought we were doing okay.

24
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:36,578
[JAO] Then one day,

25
00:00:36,911 --> 00:00:38,329
she said she wanted to go on a solo trip

26
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:39,873
here in Siargao for a week.

27
00:00:39,914 --> 00:00:41,499
[KARA] I don’t need to know all these things.

28
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:42,708
Stop dumping it on me!

29
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:43,959
I'm not your therapist.

30
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,377
[JAO] Siargao!

31
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,464
Please bring Allie back to me!

32
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:50,341
I’ll search all of Siargao if I have to.

33
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:52,635
It’s hard to find someone who doesn’t want to be found.

34
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:54,304
[RINGING]

35
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:55,221
Kara?

36
00:00:55,222 --> 00:00:56,347
[KARA] Allie?

37
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:58,391
He’s here.

38
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:02,562
Look,

39
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:04,314
if you don't want to talk to him,

40
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:07,233
I'll find a way.

41
00:01:11,946 --> 00:01:14,240
[KARA] I think the curse has a third version.

42
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:19,078
That is, you experience both love and loss.

43
00:01:22,081 --> 00:01:24,083
-I’ll settle the bill. -Sure.

44
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:26,503
- It’s so nice. But later, - Thank you.

45
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:27,754
- we’ll go to Katig. - Last round?

46
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:28,755
Okay?

47
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:30,924
Kara!

48
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:32,341
I’ll take them to Katig, okay?

49
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:32,884
Okay.

50
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:34,760
- Okay, bye! - Take care!

51
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:36,137
Let’s go to Katig?

52
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:37,722
- Okay! - Let’s go!

53
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:38,889
[BARTENDER] Here’s your change, ma’am.

54
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:40,141
[KARA] Thanks.

55
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:50,902
Who’s that?

56
00:01:51,110 --> 00:01:52,111
Oh, her?

57
00:01:52,695 --> 00:01:55,073
She’s been coming here for two days now.

58
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:58,201
- You used to be just like her. - Hey.

59
00:01:58,743 --> 00:02:00,662
Give me a beer.

60
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:04,415
- Thanks. - Thank you, ma’am.

61
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:10,547
Hi!

62
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:12,549
Are you alone?

63
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:14,467
Can I sit with you?

64
00:02:14,509 --> 00:02:15,510
Yeah.

65
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:27,939
You don’t have to talk.

66
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,065
But...

67
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,441
I’m Kara.

68
00:02:33,736 --> 00:02:34,737
Allie.

69
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:41,995
[ALLIE SIGHS]

70
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:43,913
Did you fight?

71
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,791
Worse.

72
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,168
I ghosted him.

73
00:02:52,088 --> 00:02:54,424
Maybe you just needed some time.

74
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:58,093
I don’t know. I don't know if I'll ever

75
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:00,096
be able to face him, to be honest.

76
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:03,474
I don’t think I can.

77
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:07,103
I don't know how I can tell him that…

78
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:09,898
I'm done.

79
00:03:10,732 --> 00:03:12,817
Is that why you came to Siargao?

80
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:16,613
Well…

81
00:03:19,657 --> 00:03:21,658
I just thought…

82
00:03:21,659 --> 00:03:23,368
maybe I just need a vacation

83
00:03:23,369 --> 00:03:27,205
because I’ve just been feeling so lost,

84
00:03:27,206 --> 00:03:29,208
and so empty.

85
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:31,002
But…

86
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:35,505
I don’t know, the past few days here, without him,

87
00:03:35,506 --> 00:03:36,507
I’ve just…

88
00:03:39,093 --> 00:03:43,263
I realized I feel so suffocated in our relationship.

89
00:03:43,264 --> 00:03:45,266
Like, I can’t do it anymore.

90
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:54,108
Thank you.

91
00:04:06,245 --> 00:04:08,957
I've been trying to get him to come to Siargao forever.

92
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:11,626
But he always had an excuse,

93
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:14,337
something else was more important.

94
00:04:15,964 --> 00:04:17,465
You know, at first,

95
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:20,134
I thought

96
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:21,469
maybe he was just really busy,

97
00:04:21,511 --> 00:04:24,180
he had a lot going on, right?

98
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:25,473
But then it became a pattern.

99
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:27,433
It was always the same.

100
00:04:27,475 --> 00:04:29,477
Every time I wanted to do something,

101
00:04:29,852 --> 00:04:30,937
he’d just brush it off.

102
00:04:30,979 --> 00:04:34,899
Or he’d make up an excuse…

103
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:36,066
just to stay in control.

104
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:37,652
He always had to be in control.

105
00:04:37,694 --> 00:04:39,696
What about what I want?

106
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:45,118
As if he knows what you want better than yourself.

107
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:47,161
Yes, exactly.

108
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:49,162
Meanwhile,

109
00:04:49,163 --> 00:04:51,666
you’re always thinking about what he wants.

110
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:54,085
You’re willing to give up what you want

111
00:04:54,419 --> 00:04:56,796
to do what’s best for him.

112
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:00,967
Well… not really.

113
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:02,343
But…

114
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,429
Whatever!

115
00:05:04,887 --> 00:05:06,431
I don’t know what I want anymore.

116
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:07,807
No idea!

117
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:09,726
All I know is

118
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:12,061
just for the short time that I’ve been here,

119
00:05:12,937 --> 00:05:14,272
away from him,

120
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:16,691
I realized that

121
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:18,775
I don't need permission to be myself.

122
00:05:18,776 --> 00:05:20,153
To do what I want.

123
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:26,367
Why don’t you just tell him the truth?

124
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:28,786
So you’re not hiding anymore.

125
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:31,372
You don’t know Jao.

126
00:05:31,873 --> 00:05:34,834
He’ll try to fix it or he’ll try to fix me

127
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:38,129
because I’m always the problem.

128
00:05:38,504 --> 00:05:39,671
But I’m done with that.

129
00:05:39,672 --> 00:05:40,757
I’m done!

130
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:43,383
I’m so sure that I’m done!

131
00:05:43,384 --> 00:05:45,386
We’re just going in circles.

132
00:05:45,762 --> 00:05:48,139
- He sounds toxic then. - Yes!

133
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,391
All I know is,

134
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:52,810
I feel free.

135
00:05:52,852 --> 00:05:55,438
And I haven’t felt like this in a very long time.

136
00:05:58,066 --> 00:05:59,567
Is that all?

137
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:10,244
[AHON BY JL]

138
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:36,372
Why did we stop?

139
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:38,790
I just need five minutes.

140
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,793
I’m just going to grab some things.

141
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,884
Sorry about what I said earlier.

142
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:53,472
I was just telling you all that

143
00:07:54,682 --> 00:07:56,851
to give you some context.

144
00:07:58,352 --> 00:08:02,190
That I’m not only doing this just for the heck of it.

145
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:06,861
I’m doing all of this

146
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:09,322
because I love Allie.

147
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,036
I’ll help you. But...

148
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:19,999
please spare me the details.

149
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,421
[JAO SIGHS]

150
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:29,675
I’ll leave a bad review for both Katig and you.

151
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:38,517
[JAO LAUGHS]

152
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,685
Just kidding!

153
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,770
You showed zero empathy.

154
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:43,356
I just told you a really dramatic story.

155
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:45,399
But, promise, that was all real.

156
00:08:47,151 --> 00:08:48,444
Just make it up to me.

157
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:52,949
- Nice. - Sure.

158
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:56,660
You don’t have to get out,

159
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:58,496
but if you want to stretch your legs,

160
00:08:58,538 --> 00:08:59,705
you’re free to do so.

161
00:09:02,541 --> 00:09:03,709
Where are we anyway?

162
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:06,545
We’re at Pacifico.

163
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,005
I live here.

164
00:09:09,632 --> 00:09:11,258
Hi, Carol!

165
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:12,760
Hey, Kara!

166
00:09:15,012 --> 00:09:16,597
Let me help you!

167
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:18,766
It’s fine.

168
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:23,187
These new colors are beautiful!

169
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,438
Right?

170
00:09:24,605 --> 00:09:26,983
Ariel made that one you’re holding!

171
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:27,858
Oh!

172
00:09:27,859 --> 00:09:30,277
Not bad at all for my eldest!

173
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:31,529
[SIARGAONON] He’s amazing!

174
00:09:31,737 --> 00:09:35,324
I have to deliver these to GL.

175
00:09:36,158 --> 00:09:37,868
What? But it’s already late.

176
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:39,703
- Don’t go now! - It’s okay.

177
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:41,079
[KARA] I'm giving a ride to someone there anyway.

178
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:41,956
Who’s this?

179
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,124
Um…

180
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:44,041
Who are you?

181
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:46,043
Carol, this is Jao.

182
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:49,588
Jao, Carol. She owns Carol’s Inn.

183
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:50,840
She’s Pearl’s mom,

184
00:09:50,881 --> 00:09:52,383
our receptionist in Katig.

185
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:54,885
Nice to meet you.

186
00:09:55,219 --> 00:09:56,721
- Nice to meet you. - This place is beautiful.

187
00:09:56,762 --> 00:09:57,471
[CAROL GIGGLES]

188
00:09:57,513 --> 00:09:58,514
Just like me.

189
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:02,726
Would you like to have dinner here, Jao?

190
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:05,271
It’s too late to go to GL now.

191
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:07,648
- Let’s have dinner instead. - Sure.

192
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:09,025
Do you eat kinilaw (Filipino ceviche)?

193
00:10:09,066 --> 00:10:09,859
I'm great…

194
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:10,900
- at making kinilaw. - [JAO] Of course.

195
00:10:10,901 --> 00:10:11,569
Oh!

196
00:10:11,570 --> 00:10:13,821
Okay, then. Let’s try it.

197
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,280
All right.

198
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,282
This one.

199
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:17,742
Are you selling these?

200
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:19,577
Me?

201
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:20,785
Oh, you’re a funny one!

202
00:10:20,786 --> 00:10:21,912
Not me!

203
00:10:21,954 --> 00:10:23,705
Kara made these.

204
00:10:23,706 --> 00:10:26,334
It’s her passion project, turned into a business.

205
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:28,793
She owns that shop outside.

206
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,005
It’s called Gaia. Pretty, huh?

207
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:34,175
Oh, right! Dinner.

208
00:10:34,216 --> 00:10:35,634
- I’ll take care of this. - I’ll leave you to it.

209
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:36,885
I’ll just fix us some dinner.

210
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:37,762
All right.

211
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:41,349
Gaia?

212
00:10:41,849 --> 00:10:43,809
Gaia. Mother Earth.

213
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:46,854
Nice name. Very unique.

214
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:48,814
Thanks.

215
00:10:50,524 --> 00:10:51,150
You know what,

216
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,735
given the right promotion and

217
00:10:52,777 --> 00:10:54,070
marketing campaign,

218
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:56,155
your brand could really take off.

219
00:10:56,572 --> 00:10:59,450
Stuff like these are big in retail now.

220
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:01,660
Stuff like what?

221
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:04,580
Like these. Slow fashion,

222
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:07,958
sustainable, zero-waste, organic, the works.

223
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:11,670
I don’t do this because it’s trendy.

224
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:13,713
Sustainability shouldn’t be a trend.

225
00:11:13,714 --> 00:11:15,299
It should be the norm.

226
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:18,636
I agree.

227
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:21,514
Let’s go?

228
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:23,766
Hold on.

229
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,351
[JAO CLEARS THROAT]

230
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:27,853
I want to buy a sarong for Allie.

231
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:28,979
You can choose.

232
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:30,648
Okay, um…

233
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:32,483
What’s her favorite color?

234
00:11:35,444 --> 00:11:36,445
I don’t know.

235
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:39,698
You don’t know your girlfriend’s favorite color?

236
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:40,616
[JAO LAUGHS]

237
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:41,742
Well…

238
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:43,868
It changes every month.

239
00:11:43,869 --> 00:11:46,789
I can’t keep up with her.

240
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:51,043
Um, fine.

241
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:52,920
You can get this.

242
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:57,299
Dyed using talisay leaves.

243
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:01,011
The trees you see on the beaches here.

244
00:12:03,264 --> 00:12:04,265
Nice.

245
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:05,558
[KARA] Thanks.

246
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:06,851
How much?

247
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:08,102
3,200 pesos.

248
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:09,103
3,200 pesos?

249
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:10,146
Yeah.

250
00:12:11,188 --> 00:12:11,856
Why?

251
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:13,356
Just because it's local and handmade,

252
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:14,483
you think it would be cheap?

253
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:16,944
[KARA] I mean, the fabric’s nice.

254
00:12:17,611 --> 00:12:18,945
And I used natural dye.

255
00:12:18,946 --> 00:12:22,450
Plus, I've put in a lot of passion and artistry into it.

256
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,368
You didn't let me finish. I meant to say 3,200 pesos?

257
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:26,495
You deserve it.

258
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:36,672
[WAVES CRASHING]

259
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:37,840
[WATER SPLASHES]

260
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:42,636
Do you think Allie will go here?

261
00:12:44,138 --> 00:12:48,267
Magpupungko is a popular tourist site.

262
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,896
It’s one of the best spots on the island.

263
00:12:55,649 --> 00:12:57,151
See that rock?

264
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:59,820
That’s the Magpupungko Rock.

265
00:13:00,404 --> 00:13:03,073
Magpupungko means “squatting.”

266
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:08,704
I don’t think she’ll come here.

267
00:13:10,706 --> 00:13:12,374
You give up too easily!

268
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,835
At least check out the rock pools.

269
00:13:17,713 --> 00:13:18,964
Kara, I’m sorry.

270
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:22,051
I didn’t come here for vacation.

271
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,428
I’m here to find her, and besides,

272
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:25,721
I know Allie.

273
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:28,891
She won’t come here because she’s scared of waves.

274
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,435
You think she’d come to Siargao

275
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:32,895
if she was scared of waves?

276
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:37,900
[KARA AND ALLIE LAUGHING]

277
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:41,111
Magpupungko is my favorite spot.

278
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:44,907
I always bring my guests here.

279
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:46,325
Because it’s so pretty.

280
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,663
If I were still with my ex, I wouldn’t have come here.

281
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:53,332
What? Why? How lame.

282
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:54,500
[ALLIE LAUGHS]

283
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:56,459
I mean, don’t get me wrong, okay?

284
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,753
Jao is actually nice.

285
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:00,964
And he’s gentle,

286
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:03,216
thoughtful, yada-yada-yada.

287
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:05,052
He never gets mad.

288
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:08,722
But, I don’t know. There’s a part of him…

289
00:14:09,473 --> 00:14:11,850
that doesn’t like being told no.

290
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:14,478
It’s like…

291
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:16,145
He has this way of making you feel guilty

292
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:18,148
if you don’t do what he wants.

293
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,442
Do you get what I mean?

294
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:23,444
And he has this favorite line,

295
00:14:23,445 --> 00:14:26,739
“Listen to me so you don’t get hurt.”

296
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:27,782
Really?

297
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:29,617
As if I'm some five year old kid.

298
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:31,120
That’s weird.

299
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:37,710
[JAO] Actually, I made a list

300
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:40,878
of all the possible places Allie might go to.

301
00:14:40,879 --> 00:14:42,339
[KARA] I'm the tour guide, right?

302
00:14:43,173 --> 00:14:45,676
I know Siargao better than you.

303
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:47,885
I’m just trying to help.

304
00:14:47,886 --> 00:14:49,138
By taking my job?

305
00:14:50,889 --> 00:14:51,890
Let me see.

306
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:58,272
All that’s missing are timestamps.

307
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:01,233
Actually, good idea. I’ll add them.

308
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:02,443
You’re joking, right?

309
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:08,616
You know, most people come to Siargao to slow down.

310
00:15:11,910 --> 00:15:13,287
But I’m not most people.

311
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:17,124
I told you, this is not a vacation trip for me.

312
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:20,878
So, come on. Let’s not waste time.

313
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:25,716
[JAO] You might have seen her around.

314
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:27,426
I don't think I would be able to remember

315
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:29,094
with all the tourists who come here.

316
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,430
All right. Thanks.

317
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:52,701
Excuse me. Can I ask you something?

318
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:54,953
Have you seen this girl?

319
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,081
No.

320
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:58,374
Thanks.

321
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:05,422
Next stop?

322
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:07,216
Maybe we can continue tomorrow?

323
00:16:07,341 --> 00:16:09,467
I still have to finish some work tonight

324
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:10,511
Okay then. Let's go.

325
00:16:12,596 --> 00:16:13,514
Are these tuwai (Shellfish)?

326
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:14,598
Yes, sir.

327
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,641
I’ll have one.

328
00:16:15,849 --> 00:16:17,559
- Help yourself. - Want one?

329
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:19,978
I don’t eat those.

330
00:16:20,521 --> 00:16:21,563
Vegan.

331
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:23,565
Oh.

332
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:25,650
Sorry, I didn’t know. What about drinks?

333
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,403
-Anything? - No, I’m fine.

334
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:31,532
One coconut juice and a soda, please.

335
00:16:31,573 --> 00:16:33,367
[SIARGAONAN] Can you please get me a coconut?

336
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:42,125
[VENDOR] Get a soda.

337
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:43,127
[KARA] Thanks.

338
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:56,974
When you eat tuwai (shellfish), you need to drink soda with it.

339
00:16:57,015 --> 00:16:59,351
If you just drink water, you might throw up.

340
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:02,062
Did you do a research on that?

341
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:05,524
How much?

342
00:17:05,816 --> 00:17:07,776
80 pesos, sir. Including the coconut.

343
00:17:07,818 --> 00:17:08,652
- I’ll pay. - And the tuwai.

344
00:17:08,653 --> 00:17:09,653
No, I’ve got it.

345
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:14,533
Thanks, ma’am.

346
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:18,077
- [VENDOR] I have toothpicks for that. - [ALLIE] I'll have some. Thanks!

347
00:17:18,078 --> 00:17:19,079
Add some vinegar.

348
00:17:23,959 --> 00:17:26,085
- Hey-! - Joking!

349
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:27,755
[KARA AND ALLIE LAUGHING]

350
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:32,300
You know, Jao never lets me pay.

351
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:33,427
Like, never.

352
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:35,721
Really? Lucky you.

353
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:36,722
[KARA LAUGHS]

354
00:17:36,723 --> 00:17:39,016
Honestly, it was frustrating.

355
00:17:39,057 --> 00:17:41,351
You know what I mean?

356
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:45,022
Sometimes I just want to share or contribute.

357
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:46,273
But I can’t.

358
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:48,901
I'm not allowed to do what I want.

359
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:50,986
What do you mean, as in everything?

360
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,155
He controls everything.

361
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:56,199
Plans, schedules, what I eat, what I do-

362
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,284
Everything!

363
00:17:59,077 --> 00:17:59,578
Keep the change.

364
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:00,913
[SIARGAONON] Thank you very much, sir.

365
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:19,765
Thank you.

366
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:27,147
You look exhausted.

367
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,817
I am.

368
00:18:30,776 --> 00:18:31,777
Why?

369
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:37,491
Jao is stubborn.

370
00:18:38,325 --> 00:18:40,702
He thinks Allie’s just playing hard to get.

371
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:43,247
He won’t stop until he finds her.

372
00:18:45,874 --> 00:18:48,126
Allie’s that important to him?

373
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,590
Or maybe…

374
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:57,678
he just can’t accept that his girlfriend left him.

375
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:01,849
Allie’s right.

376
00:19:02,224 --> 00:19:04,601
He won’t take no for an answer.

377
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:07,563
Oh...

378
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:09,815
Is that a bad thing?

379
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:12,985
What if he’s been right all along?

380
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:16,780
How?

381
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:19,032
He can’t always be right.

382
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:22,077
He should try listening to his girlfriend.

383
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:30,919
Where did you take him today?

384
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:34,506
Where did I take him?

385
00:19:35,591 --> 00:19:37,759
He’s so controlling,

386
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,762
he chose where we’d go.

387
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:43,390
I had a hard time throwing him off.

388
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:46,018
I keep thinking about what Allie said.

389
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:48,103
Everything he does

390
00:19:48,395 --> 00:19:51,148
is planned down to the minute.

391
00:19:53,317 --> 00:19:55,319
[SIARGAONON] So he’s organized.

392
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:59,031
At least time isn’t wasted.

393
00:20:00,157 --> 00:20:01,158
Really?

394
00:20:02,743 --> 00:20:04,118
[SIARGAONON] Honestly,

395
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:06,413
he doesn’t sound like a bad person.

396
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:09,583
He just wants to find Allie.

397
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,544
But I promised Allie I will help her.

398
00:20:15,797 --> 00:20:16,798
Just...

399
00:20:17,466 --> 00:20:20,594
Just make sure, okay?

400
00:20:21,261 --> 00:20:23,555
That you have sound judgment.

401
00:20:24,431 --> 00:20:26,934
You might regret it later.

402
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:29,645
[PHONE PINGS]

403
00:20:33,190 --> 00:20:36,234
[ALLIE] Let's meet.

404
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:39,363
Do we have a spare motorcycle?

405
00:20:46,954 --> 00:20:49,915
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

406
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:53,251
Kara!

407
00:20:56,171 --> 00:20:57,381
Sir, your order!

408
00:20:57,422 --> 00:20:58,674
I’ll come back for it!

409
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:26,743
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

410
00:22:06,324 --> 00:22:07,325
[JAO] Allie?

411
00:22:20,797 --> 00:22:21,631
Allie?

412
00:22:42,903 --> 00:22:44,362
[JAO] I don’t give up easily.

413
00:22:44,696 --> 00:22:47,074
It's one of the qualities Allie liked about me.

414
00:22:47,115 --> 00:22:48,283
That’s how it is.

415
00:22:48,325 --> 00:22:50,452
You have to leave where you’re from

416
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,287
to learn how to stand on your own.

417
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:53,537
[HAN BIN] Jao!

418
00:22:53,538 --> 00:22:55,247
This is Quinito,

419
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:56,917
best chef in Manila.

420
00:22:56,958 --> 00:22:58,167
And this is Jao.

421
00:22:58,168 --> 00:22:59,211
- Hi. Jao. - 'Sup, brother?

422
00:22:59,252 --> 00:22:59,920
Nice to meet you.

423
00:22:59,921 --> 00:23:01,630
[HAN BIN] Are you settling in just fine?

424
00:23:01,671 --> 00:23:03,423
If you need anything just let me know.

425
00:23:03,465 --> 00:23:05,384
No worries. I’m good, brother.

426
00:23:05,425 --> 00:23:06,593
[ARIEL] Han Bin oppa!

427
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:08,804
I didn’ t know you had such a good singing voice!

428
00:23:08,845 --> 00:23:09,887
- Thank you. - I’ll upload a video

429
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:11,556
of your performance on my vlog, okay?

430
00:23:11,598 --> 00:23:12,682
No, no, no, no!

431
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:14,059
Please don’t do that.

432
00:23:14,142 --> 00:23:15,267
Delete the video.

433
00:23:15,268 --> 00:23:17,104
- Allie! - Kara!

434
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:19,105
Oh, my gosh!

435
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:20,773
Thank you so much for helping me!

436
00:23:20,774 --> 00:23:22,526
Jao really cares for you a lot.

437
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:24,569
He loves you so much, Allie.
